Defendant Terrance Lee Lawrence in court with attorney Joseph Edward Schubert.  
Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 36 MONTHS with credit for 6 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 18 MONTHS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*No use or possession of any illegal substances;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No conduct rising to the level of probable cause;
*Perform 40 hours of community service;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay fine of $500.00 plus all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of probation period-any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment- agent to determine monthly payment plan;

Defendant is informed he may not possess and/or own any firearms.
Defendant is informed he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been reinstated.  Appeal rights given.  Defense motion for expungement denied by the Court.
